      <img src="images/teuta.png">
      <div>
        <h3>Teuta Elezaj - Founder and President, C.S. with a Minor in Mathematics</h3>
        <p>Hello everyone! My name is Teuta Elezaj and I am a junior studying Computer Science! My parents immigrated here from Kosovo and I am a first-generation American and college student. I originally enrolled at SJU as a BioMed major, but I quickly realized it wasn't the path for me. It took me about a year to have the guts to change my path, but I've been a CS student for 3 semesters now and I have finally found passion in my work. Being that I have been in a couple of different STEM fields, and in high school I was also in a STEM program, I've been around men for the vast majority of my life and have been confronted with several different instances of misogynistic conduct and comments. I hope that this club can serve as a safe space for you all to thrive and succeed, and I want us to create an environment where motivation is a permanent feeling!
          I have a cat that I adopted about four months ago and a younger brother! My current  career goal is to be a software engineer, and in the future I hope to integrate my passion for business with my coding abilities. Weightlifting is a huge passion of mine and in my free time, I'm usually working on a coding project (like this website!) or watching Survivor!</p>
        <a href="https://linktr.ee/teutaelezaj" target="_blank" class="btn">Contact Me!</a>
